WEBVTT

00:02.030 --> 00:06.570
<i>* MTV *</i>

00:06.770 --> 00:08.640
I can't stop it.

00:08.840 --> 00:09.810
I can help you.

00:10.010 --> 00:10.840
[roars]

00:11.040 --> 00:12.410
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:12.610 --> 00:13.710
<i>Everyone around you,</i>

00:13.910 --> 00:15.480
<i>he'll kill them all,</i>

00:15.680 --> 00:17.610
and then he'll come for you.

00:17.810 --> 00:19.120
<i>You're superstitious enough</i>

00:19.320 --> 00:21.080
to load your gun
with silver bullets.

00:21.280 --> 00:23.590
Let's catch a werewolf.

00:23.790 --> 00:25.460
It's right behind me!

00:25.650 --> 00:28.360
- [roars]
- Shut the door!

00:28.560 --> 00:29.790
I can't lose my kids.

00:29.990 --> 00:31.230
What are you not telling me?

00:34.260 --> 00:37.000
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:37.200 --> 00:43.710
<i>* *</i>

00:44.740 --> 00:47.280
[breathing heavily]

00:47.480 --> 00:51.450
<i>* *</i>

00:51.650 --> 00:53.880
- [distorted, echoing]
- I think...

00:54.080 --> 00:55.720
What did you do?

00:57.090 --> 00:58.750
- We need to get him
to the hospital!

00:58.950 --> 01:01.460
- If we pull the knife
and he changes back--

01:01.660 --> 01:02.460
I gotta pull the knife.

01:02.660 --> 01:03.760
It's too dangerous.

01:03.960 --> 01:05.060
Everett...

01:05.260 --> 01:06.760
- wait.
- I'm doing it!

01:06.960 --> 01:13.070
<i>* *</i>

01:16.270 --> 01:19.110
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:19.310 --> 01:26.180
<i>* *</i>

02:18.470 --> 02:21.940
<i>[ominous music]</i>

02:22.140 --> 02:24.940
[lights buzzing]

02:25.140 --> 02:32.010
<i>* *</i>

02:38.450 --> 02:41.190
[monitor beeping]

02:41.390 --> 02:48.260
<i>* *</i>

03:37.880 --> 03:40.520
How you feeling, Everett?

03:40.720 --> 03:42.720
[sighs]

03:42.920 --> 03:43.920
Let me get you some water.

03:44.120 --> 03:45.720
You're probably
a little dehydrated.

03:45.920 --> 03:47.760
It's all perfectly normal.

03:47.960 --> 03:49.090
Now, if you're comfortable,

03:49.290 --> 03:51.260
we can bring your parents
in now for the follow-up.

03:51.460 --> 03:53.600
Mr. and Mrs. Lang, come on in.

03:53.800 --> 04:00.870
<i>* *</i>

04:17.350 --> 04:18.850
- [normally]
- Hey, Ev.

04:20.490 --> 04:21.720
How you doing?

04:23.430 --> 04:24.830
He looks drugged.

04:25.030 --> 04:26.400
- Well, your son
was just given 70 milligrams

04:26.600 --> 04:28.200
of a rather powerful
anesthetic.

04:28.400 --> 04:30.170
I would say Everett's
quite drugged.

04:30.370 --> 04:31.600
- That's not--

04:31.800 --> 04:33.800
- He's here for the therapeutic
benefit, remember?

04:34.000 --> 04:35.270
Well, I certainly hope so.

04:35.470 --> 04:37.370
Because otherwise,
we just spent $3,000

04:37.570 --> 04:39.440
to get our son high.

04:39.640 --> 04:41.680
- Everett.
- That's not my name.

04:41.880 --> 04:44.480
- Is he drugged
or brain-damaged?

04:44.680 --> 04:46.220
Everett.

04:46.420 --> 04:47.450
Do you know where you are?

04:47.650 --> 04:49.590
- My name--
- Do you have any nausea?

04:49.790 --> 04:50.590
- My name is--

04:50.790 --> 04:52.460
Is this normal?

04:52.650 --> 04:53.960
Doesn't seem normal.

04:54.160 --> 04:55.960
Or particularly therapeutic.

04:57.590 --> 04:58.630
Everett.

04:58.830 --> 05:00.000
Do you feel dizzy?

05:00.200 --> 05:02.200
Headache, heart palpitations?

05:02.400 --> 05:04.930
No.

05:05.130 --> 05:07.400
- Did you feel any anxiety
during the session,

05:07.600 --> 05:09.100
experience any hallucinations?

05:09.300 --> 05:11.410
<i>* *</i>

05:11.610 --> 05:12.740
I saw fire.

05:12.940 --> 05:17.750
<i>* *</i>

05:17.950 --> 05:19.180
What kind of fire?

05:19.380 --> 05:21.250
Wildfire.

05:21.450 --> 05:25.220
<i>* *</i>

05:25.420 --> 05:26.620
You know what?

05:26.820 --> 05:28.890
I don't think we accurately
estimated his tolerance.

05:29.090 --> 05:30.260
- Another round
of 70 milligrams?

05:30.460 --> 05:31.490
Make it 90.

05:31.690 --> 05:32.900
- Is that safe?
- Absolutely.

05:33.090 --> 05:35.430
The dose we give for pain
management is much higher.

05:35.630 --> 05:42.200
<i>* *</i>

05:51.350 --> 05:52.480
Wait.

05:52.680 --> 05:53.920
Wait, I--

05:54.120 --> 05:55.690
I don't want any more.

05:55.880 --> 05:57.290
[breathing heavily]

05:57.490 --> 05:58.950
[groans]

06:01.090 --> 06:05.030
[screams]

06:05.230 --> 06:08.530
[roars]

06:08.730 --> 06:11.770
[thunder rumbling]

06:14.000 --> 06:16.240
Come on, give me the phone.

06:16.440 --> 06:18.670
I said no.

06:18.870 --> 06:20.980
- Why not?
- Because it's private!

06:21.180 --> 06:23.250
I'm allowed one privacy
in my life.

06:23.440 --> 06:26.010
- You let Blake look
at your phone, right, Blake?

06:28.620 --> 06:30.650
- God, I let Blake take
my phone when I'm driving

06:30.850 --> 06:32.120
and I need her
to send a text for me.

06:32.320 --> 06:34.120
- Oh, she can look at it
but not me?

06:34.320 --> 06:35.990
- Yeah, 'cause she's not
searching through my messages.

06:36.190 --> 06:39.860
- What's the problem with me
looking at my wife's messages?

06:40.060 --> 06:42.700
- The problem is, you're
not looking; you're digging.

06:42.900 --> 06:44.530
You're trying to find
something that justifies

06:44.730 --> 06:45.840
your paranoid bullshit.

06:46.030 --> 06:48.000
- It's not paranoid
if it's true!

06:49.970 --> 06:52.540
Danny, hey.

06:52.740 --> 06:53.840
Take your fidget cube.

06:54.040 --> 06:54.880
[cube clattering]

06:55.080 --> 06:57.050
All right, give me the phone.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.550
- You are not looking
at my fucking phone, Rob!

06:59.750 --> 07:00.980
Give it to me.

07:01.180 --> 07:02.020
- [thumping]
- Hey, don't do that.

07:02.220 --> 07:03.590
Remember, no hitting.

07:03.790 --> 07:05.660
[thumping continues]
Danny, I--

07:05.850 --> 07:07.460
- [whimpers]
- No hitting.

07:07.660 --> 07:08.760
Give me the phone!

07:08.960 --> 07:12.090
- No!
- I said Danny, no hitting.

07:12.290 --> 07:13.460
Give me the goddamn phone!

07:13.660 --> 07:16.330
- Danny, no hitting!
- Give me the fucking--

07:16.530 --> 07:17.470
[snarling] No hitting!

07:17.670 --> 07:18.600
Give it to me!

07:18.800 --> 07:19.800
[horn blares]

07:20.000 --> 07:20.800
[glass shattering]

07:21.000 --> 07:23.110
[bullets clattering]

07:33.780 --> 07:36.890
[breathing heavily]

07:40.020 --> 07:42.890
<i>[eerie music]</i>

07:43.090 --> 07:45.900
[floorboards creaking]

07:46.090 --> 07:53.140
<i>* *</i>

07:56.970 --> 07:58.840
Keep the gun loaded.

07:59.040 --> 08:01.540
Keep an extra two clips
with it.

08:02.710 --> 08:04.510
[bullets rattling]

08:04.710 --> 08:05.580
Keep it close.

08:08.250 --> 08:10.490
- Want to tell me
what's going on?

08:10.690 --> 08:12.290
It's about last week.

08:12.490 --> 08:14.290
- You mean what happened
to Luna's horse?

08:14.490 --> 08:16.490
It wasn't an accident.

08:17.430 --> 08:19.500
What did she do?

08:19.700 --> 08:22.630
- Something a nine-year-old
girl shouldn't be able to do.

08:22.830 --> 08:25.330
She doesn't remember doing it--

08:25.530 --> 08:28.270
doesn't remember the blood,
the body...

08:28.470 --> 08:31.210
<i>* *</i>

08:31.410 --> 08:33.110
none of it.

08:33.310 --> 08:34.710
Does Harlan know about it?

08:34.910 --> 08:37.280
Harlan?

08:37.480 --> 08:38.850
No.

08:39.050 --> 08:41.420
I think it's better
if it stays that way.

08:41.620 --> 08:43.290
Harlan.

08:43.480 --> 08:48.790
<i>* *</i>

08:48.990 --> 08:50.760
Go back to sleep, Luna.

08:50.960 --> 08:51.990
Did something happen?

08:52.190 --> 08:58.370
<i>* *</i>

08:58.570 --> 09:00.470
It's not your problem.

09:00.670 --> 09:02.740
Did I do something?

09:02.940 --> 09:06.840
- No it's--
look, it's my problem.

09:07.040 --> 09:09.850
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:10.050 --> 09:11.950
<i>* *</i>

09:12.150 --> 09:13.780
Let's go back to bed.

09:13.980 --> 09:20.590
* *

09:27.560 --> 09:30.400
[pencils scratching]

09:30.600 --> 09:36.300
<i>* *</i>

09:37.870 --> 09:40.740
<i>[eerie music]</i>

09:40.940 --> 09:46.080
<i>* *</i>

09:46.280 --> 09:49.490
- What do you think
you're doing?

09:49.680 --> 09:51.920
What?

09:52.120 --> 09:54.290
Why do you keep drawing me?

09:54.490 --> 09:58.760
<i>* *</i>

09:58.960 --> 10:00.500
Give me that.

10:00.700 --> 10:07.570
<i>* *</i>

10:11.940 --> 10:15.710
<i>[wolf growling]</i>

10:15.910 --> 10:17.610
<i>It was a wolf!</i>

10:17.810 --> 10:19.880
[panting]

10:20.080 --> 10:21.780
When we were on that bus...

10:21.980 --> 10:24.650
<i>* *</i>

10:24.850 --> 10:27.920
When all the animals came
running out of the woods...

10:28.120 --> 10:30.160
<i>* *</i>

10:30.360 --> 10:31.790
They were scared of you.

10:31.990 --> 10:34.630
<i>* *</i>

10:34.830 --> 10:36.830
No, it wasn't me.

10:37.030 --> 10:38.500
You killed a cop.

10:38.700 --> 10:41.600
You killed my doctor
and a nurse.

10:41.800 --> 10:43.170
You killed Phoebe.

10:43.370 --> 10:46.940
- It was the fire.
The wolf, he got caught.

10:47.140 --> 10:50.210
[fire whooshing]

10:52.150 --> 10:53.620
I got caught.

10:53.820 --> 10:57.920
<i>* *</i>

10:58.120 --> 10:59.790
I got caught in the fire.

10:59.990 --> 11:02.690
But the fire didn't kill you.

11:02.890 --> 11:04.330
It changed you.

11:05.790 --> 11:07.000
That's why I brought this.

11:07.200 --> 11:14.270
<i>* *</i>

11:15.100 --> 11:18.040
[breathing heavily]

11:24.150 --> 11:27.220
- You know, your friends
don't like me.

11:29.180 --> 11:30.720
I don't like you.

11:32.490 --> 11:34.490
- They're not gonna accept me
as part of your pack.

11:34.690 --> 11:36.790
<i>* *</i>

11:36.990 --> 11:38.590
I don't want them to.

11:38.790 --> 11:40.530
<i>* *</i>

11:40.730 --> 11:43.000
- How come?
- Because you're a threat.

11:43.200 --> 11:45.070
<i>* *</i>

11:45.270 --> 11:47.700
And I'll kill anyone
who threatens my pack.

11:49.440 --> 11:50.870
Why?

11:51.070 --> 11:53.340
[breathing heavily]

11:53.540 --> 11:55.010
Because I have to kill.

11:55.210 --> 11:57.210
<i>* *</i>

11:57.410 --> 11:59.510
Because I can't help myself.

12:01.750 --> 12:03.590
If I'm gonna die,

12:03.780 --> 12:06.160
then there's nothing I can do
about it.

12:06.350 --> 12:09.060
<i>* *</i>

12:09.260 --> 12:10.460
[snarling] You can run.

12:10.660 --> 12:12.930
[gunshots]

12:13.130 --> 12:15.900
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:16.100 --> 12:23.170
<i>* *</i>

12:27.040 --> 12:29.910
[snarling]

12:30.110 --> 12:34.480
<i>* *</i>

12:34.680 --> 12:35.850
[growls]

12:36.050 --> 12:43.130
<i>* *</i>

12:50.370 --> 12:53.200
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:53.400 --> 12:55.810
<i>* *</i>

12:56.000 --> 12:57.110
Wait, I know you.

12:57.310 --> 13:01.210
<i>* *</i>

13:01.410 --> 13:03.750
You're like me.
We--we're the same.

13:03.950 --> 13:06.450
<i>* *</i>

13:06.650 --> 13:09.820
It's OK.
I--I'm not gonna hurt you.

13:10.020 --> 13:11.150
That's right.

13:11.350 --> 13:12.760
He'll rip your throat out
so fast,

13:12.950 --> 13:13.720
you won't feel a thing.

13:13.920 --> 13:16.790
[gunshots]

13:18.390 --> 13:19.260
<i>- We have to pull</i>
<i>the knife out!</i>

13:19.460 --> 13:20.600
<i>Everett, wait.</i>

13:20.800 --> 13:22.060
<i>I'm doing it!</i>

13:22.260 --> 13:23.570
<i>- If we pull the knife</i>
<i>and he changes back--</i>

13:23.760 --> 13:25.600
Don't!

13:33.410 --> 13:34.280
- Careful, put him down.
Put him down.

13:34.480 --> 13:35.440
Shit!

13:35.640 --> 13:37.450
<i>[tense music]</i>

13:37.650 --> 13:38.550
We need him up here.

13:38.750 --> 13:39.750
Shit!

13:39.950 --> 13:42.750
[gasping]

13:42.950 --> 13:44.690
Oh, God.

13:44.890 --> 13:45.860
Look out.

13:46.050 --> 13:46.990
- What the fuck's
happening to him?

13:47.190 --> 13:49.020
- [groaning]
- How should I know?

13:49.220 --> 13:53.030
- Just hold him.
- Guys, look.

13:53.230 --> 13:57.330
- Look.
- [panting]

13:57.530 --> 14:00.140
Someone help me.

14:00.340 --> 14:01.040
[grunts]

14:01.240 --> 14:02.300
Oh, he's still bleeding!

14:02.500 --> 14:03.670
We need to do something
to help him!

14:03.870 --> 14:05.770
- No, we're not--

14:05.970 --> 14:07.810
we're not taking him
to a hospital.

14:08.010 --> 14:10.050
[gasping]

14:10.250 --> 14:11.310
Fuck!

14:11.510 --> 14:13.920
I can't breathe!

14:14.120 --> 14:15.780
Why can't I catch my breath?

14:15.980 --> 14:18.090
Why are you looking at me?

14:18.290 --> 14:20.720
- Because you're giving me
a panic attack.

14:20.920 --> 14:23.130
No.

14:23.320 --> 14:25.430
I'm not.

14:25.630 --> 14:26.930
<i>* *</i>

14:27.130 --> 14:28.530
Why are my hands shaking?

14:28.730 --> 14:32.170
- That's your anxiety,
not mine.

14:32.370 --> 14:39.240
<i>* *</i>

14:40.440 --> 14:41.680
- Can we stop fighting
and figure out

14:41.880 --> 14:43.580
what to do with him?

14:43.780 --> 14:46.620
- Guys, you can literally see
the silver in his blood.

14:46.810 --> 14:48.180
Oh, God.

14:48.380 --> 14:49.820
How do we know it's not
the silver that's keeping him

14:50.020 --> 14:51.050
- from changing back?
- We don't!

14:51.250 --> 14:52.190
We don't know anything!

14:52.390 --> 14:53.320
- [phone buzzing]
- Fuck.

14:53.520 --> 14:54.820
Maybe he does.

15:03.000 --> 15:06.270
<i>* *</i>

15:06.470 --> 15:07.970
<i>[phone clicks]</i>

15:09.800 --> 15:13.110
<i>- The bleeding won't stop</i>
<i>until you get that silver out.</i>

15:13.310 --> 15:16.550
<i>You have to figure out</i>
<i>how to do that first.</i>

15:16.740 --> 15:17.810
Is he dying?

15:18.010 --> 15:19.610
<i>Slowly.</i>

15:19.810 --> 15:21.950
- Then we should get him
to a hospital.

15:22.150 --> 15:23.990
<i>Of course,</i>

15:24.190 --> 15:28.560
<i>if you want everyone to know</i>
<i>his secrets--and yours.</i>

15:28.760 --> 15:30.060
Tell us what to do!

15:30.260 --> 15:32.030
<i>- Find a way to get</i>
<i>that silver out,</i>

15:32.230 --> 15:36.030
<i>or let him die</i>
<i>and break the bond.</i>

15:36.230 --> 15:37.800
- What does that mean,
break the bond?

15:38.000 --> 15:40.900
<i>- Blake feels it already,</i>
<i>don't you?</i>

15:41.100 --> 15:43.240
<i>* *</i>

15:43.440 --> 15:46.380
<i>They both do.</i>

15:46.570 --> 15:49.980
<i>You felt it as soon</i>
<i>as the knife went in.</i>

15:50.180 --> 15:52.210
<i>Now you know why Baron</i>
<i>was supposed to kill you</i>

15:52.410 --> 15:55.520
<i>the night of the full moon.</i>

15:55.720 --> 15:58.820
- My strength and her speed,
it comes from him.

15:59.020 --> 16:01.460
<i>- If Baron dies now,</i>
<i>the bond fades.</i>

16:01.660 --> 16:03.230
<i>The power fades.</i>

16:03.420 --> 16:06.200
<i>You'll be ordinary again.</i>

16:06.390 --> 16:08.900
<i>But maybe that's</i>
<i>what you want.</i>

16:09.100 --> 16:11.000
<i>Personally,</i>
<i>I don't know why anyone</i>

16:11.200 --> 16:13.540
<i>would choose to be ordinary.</i>

16:13.730 --> 16:20.540
<i>* *</i>

16:20.740 --> 16:21.710
Let him die.

16:21.910 --> 16:24.950
<i>[phone keyboard tapping]</i>

16:29.180 --> 16:30.920
Luna says it wasn't them.

16:31.120 --> 16:33.890
They don't know
anything about it.

16:34.090 --> 16:35.620
You think she's lying?

16:38.190 --> 16:40.060
I'm not sure anymore.

16:42.930 --> 16:46.270
- I'm not sure I even want
to know what happened in here.

16:46.470 --> 16:47.870
You should go home
and get some sleep.

16:48.070 --> 16:49.170
Be with the kids.

16:49.370 --> 16:51.140
I'll deal with this tomorrow.

16:51.340 --> 16:53.180
I know I'm asking a lot.

16:53.370 --> 16:55.880
If you can hold out with me
a little bit longer--

16:56.080 --> 16:59.810
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:00.010 --> 17:01.950
I'll take care of it.

17:03.620 --> 17:04.520
Go home.

17:04.720 --> 17:11.590
<i>* *</i>

17:13.560 --> 17:15.500
- We need to talk to Dad
about everything.

17:15.700 --> 17:18.530
- How about first you make sure
Austin keeps his mouth shut?

17:18.730 --> 17:20.300
- I don't think we should
tell Garrett yet.

17:20.500 --> 17:22.970
He'll probably take Baron
to the cops like Cyrus.

17:24.340 --> 17:27.180
- So what are we
gonna do with him?

17:27.380 --> 17:29.240
He's not getting any better.

17:33.850 --> 17:37.890
<i>[heartbeat thumping]</i>

17:38.090 --> 17:40.590
- His heartbeat
still sounds the same.

17:40.790 --> 17:42.060
Luna, how's he smell?

17:42.260 --> 17:44.960
Obviously not good...

17:45.160 --> 17:46.560
but I don't think he's dying.

17:46.760 --> 17:48.930
- Then he can just
stay here for now.

17:49.130 --> 17:50.130
My parents don't come home
for an hour.

17:50.330 --> 17:51.700
I can lock the door.

17:54.970 --> 17:57.170
What do you think he can do?

17:57.370 --> 17:58.670
You mean like us?

17:58.870 --> 18:00.510
You're strong.

18:00.710 --> 18:03.050
I'm fast.

18:03.240 --> 18:04.950
We each get one thing.

18:05.150 --> 18:07.180
<i>* *</i>

18:07.380 --> 18:08.850
So what do you think he can do?

18:09.050 --> 18:13.790
<i>* *</i>

18:13.990 --> 18:15.590
- We already know
what he can do.

18:15.790 --> 18:22.500
<i>* *</i>

18:23.600 --> 18:25.330
He can turn people
into werewolves.

18:25.530 --> 18:32.410
<i>* *</i>

18:38.280 --> 18:40.350
- Can't leave Baron
there all day.

18:42.180 --> 18:43.490
Can't just let him die.

18:43.680 --> 18:46.120
- If he turns back,
we can't let him live either.

18:46.320 --> 18:48.220
- OK, let's--

18:48.420 --> 18:52.890
let's talk to Dad or Prisha,
now that she knows.

18:53.090 --> 18:54.130
She always knew.

18:54.330 --> 18:58.270
<i>* *</i>

18:58.470 --> 18:59.430
What?

18:59.630 --> 19:01.800
<i>* *</i>

19:02.000 --> 19:04.440
- Remember when we saw
the marks on Garrett's truck?

19:04.640 --> 19:08.110
<i>* *</i>

19:08.310 --> 19:12.110
I said what about wolves?
She said...

19:12.310 --> 19:13.720
- A wolf couldn't
have done that.

19:13.910 --> 19:17.590
- She lied, pretended like she
didn't know anything about us.

19:17.790 --> 19:19.920
- When did she find out?
- It was after your horse.

19:20.120 --> 19:21.920
I--I heard them
talking about it.

19:22.120 --> 19:23.430
You didn't tell me?

19:23.620 --> 19:24.990
- You really wanted me
to tell you

19:25.190 --> 19:27.130
that you killed
your own horse?

19:27.330 --> 19:33.970
<i>* *</i>

19:34.170 --> 19:35.740
- I want you
to tell me the truth.

19:35.940 --> 19:40.480
<i>* *</i>

19:46.450 --> 19:49.080
[breathing heavily]

19:51.120 --> 19:52.850
[sighs]

19:53.050 --> 19:55.120
He's been like that
for hours.

19:57.930 --> 19:59.660
Maybe he's not dying.

20:01.530 --> 20:03.800
- Would it be
such a tragedy if he did?

20:05.430 --> 20:07.570
He's basically a mass murderer.

20:09.940 --> 20:13.180
- We could've killed Garrett
the other night, remember?

20:13.370 --> 20:15.540
Wouldn't that be like
the same thing?

20:17.480 --> 20:19.350
Not for you and me.

20:21.580 --> 20:22.750
We didn't ask for any of this.

20:22.950 --> 20:25.390
We didn't want any of this.

20:25.590 --> 20:28.360
I wouldn't give it back.

20:28.560 --> 20:30.960
I don't have anxiety anymore.

20:31.160 --> 20:32.630
It's gone.

20:35.300 --> 20:36.970
- Anxiety's not
such a bad thing.

20:37.160 --> 20:40.200
It's like a survival tool,
right?

20:44.410 --> 20:47.280
- Everyone always
says that to me.

20:47.480 --> 20:49.840
Use your anxiety.
It motivates you.

20:50.040 --> 20:51.580
Make your anxiety work for you.

20:51.780 --> 20:53.980
You know what anxiety
does for me?

20:54.180 --> 20:56.690
It--it makes me
want to fucking die.

20:56.880 --> 20:58.390
<i>[somber music]</i>

20:58.590 --> 21:00.860
That doesn't feel like
a survival tool to me.

21:01.060 --> 21:02.920
I'm sorry.

21:03.120 --> 21:04.530
- You really want
out of all this?

21:04.730 --> 21:06.500
- I don't want to see
my brother die.

21:06.690 --> 21:09.660
- If we get control of this,
no one has to die.

21:09.860 --> 21:12.670
We can protect anyone.

21:13.870 --> 21:16.710
We could hurt anyone.

21:16.900 --> 21:18.810
<i>[tense music]</i>

21:19.010 --> 21:21.410
- It's a minor follow-up
to what happened at the party.

21:21.610 --> 21:23.680
She's promised me the questions
are all yes and no.

21:23.880 --> 21:28.220
All the two of you say from
this moment on is yes and no.

21:28.420 --> 21:29.720
- Anything we
shouldn't tell her?

21:29.920 --> 21:32.190
I don't know.

21:32.390 --> 21:35.160
There anything you
haven't told me?

21:35.360 --> 21:36.730
Yes and no.

21:36.920 --> 21:43.770
<i>* *</i>

21:52.410 --> 21:54.880
- I'll give you
five minutes with him.

21:55.080 --> 21:56.310
Why are you doing this?

21:56.510 --> 21:57.480
You think you can listen in

21:57.680 --> 21:59.310
and get a confession
or something?

21:59.510 --> 22:02.050
- There are no listening
devices in my office.

22:02.250 --> 22:03.520
Go ahead.

22:03.720 --> 22:05.820
Turn the white noise machine on
if you want.

22:06.020 --> 22:07.390
What do you really want?

22:07.590 --> 22:09.790
- If you know something
that can help Cyrus,

22:09.990 --> 22:11.030
you need to tell me.

22:11.230 --> 22:13.060
- I know that he didn't
set the fire.

22:13.260 --> 22:14.500
How do you know that?

22:14.700 --> 22:17.800
- I'm really good at knowing
when someone's lying.

22:18.000 --> 22:19.170
He's not lying.

22:19.370 --> 22:24.270
<i>* *</i>

22:24.470 --> 22:26.680
Can you tell if I'm lying?

22:26.870 --> 22:30.110
Because I don't think Cyrus
is the arsonist either.

22:30.310 --> 22:32.010
Say that again.

22:32.210 --> 22:33.550
I...

22:33.750 --> 22:35.180
<i>[heartbeat thumping steadily]</i>

22:35.380 --> 22:37.890
Don't think...

22:38.090 --> 22:40.260
Cyrus...

22:40.450 --> 22:43.660
is...the arsonist.

22:43.860 --> 22:47.930
<i>* *</i>

22:48.130 --> 22:50.970
[indistinct chatter]

22:58.370 --> 23:00.310
You OK?

23:02.880 --> 23:07.520
<i>[static crackling]</i>

23:07.720 --> 23:10.790
<i>- I know you're not</i>
<i>the arsonist.</i>

23:10.990 --> 23:12.450
<i>- I know you're not</i>
<i>a fuck boy.</i>

23:12.650 --> 23:13.820
<i>- How'd you solve</i>
<i>that mystery?</i>

23:14.020 --> 23:15.620
<i>* *</i>

23:15.820 --> 23:19.290
<i>Because I know you like me.</i>

23:19.490 --> 23:21.430
<i>I kind of like you.</i>

23:21.630 --> 23:23.130
<i>- I think you really like me.</i>
<i>- [chuckles]</i>

23:23.330 --> 23:24.330
Fuck you.

23:24.530 --> 23:25.370
- See, we keep
talking about that,

23:25.570 --> 23:27.240
but we never get around to it.

23:27.430 --> 23:30.140
[both chuckle]

23:30.340 --> 23:32.270
[handcuffs jingle]

23:34.010 --> 23:37.880
Harlan, I know you're trying
to help me get out of this,

23:38.080 --> 23:39.010
but you shouldn't.

23:39.210 --> 23:41.320
Why not?

23:41.520 --> 23:44.690
- Remember how I said
I wasn't the arsonist

23:44.890 --> 23:47.460
and you said you were really
good at spotting a liar?

23:47.660 --> 23:52.730
Well, I wasn't lying
about being this arsonist.

23:52.930 --> 23:55.130
But...

23:55.330 --> 23:56.800
I did set a fire.

23:57.000 --> 23:59.070
<i>* *</i>

23:59.270 --> 24:01.040
- When?
- I was only nine.

24:01.240 --> 24:03.610
I was curious about my Dad,

24:03.800 --> 24:08.410
curious about fire, and...

24:08.610 --> 24:11.150
I wanted to watch
something burn.

24:11.350 --> 24:12.880
<i>* *</i>

24:13.080 --> 24:15.420
What did you burn?

24:15.620 --> 24:17.490
- You know those
housing developments

24:17.690 --> 24:21.090
that all kind of
look the same?

24:21.290 --> 24:23.490
I thought maybe no one
would notice one missing.

24:23.690 --> 24:25.630
- Did anyone get hurt?
- No, no, it was empty.

24:25.830 --> 24:26.930
But it was still arson,

24:27.130 --> 24:28.460
and it was a shit ton
of property damage.

24:28.660 --> 24:31.300
And they're gonna
use it against me and--

24:31.500 --> 24:32.730
[sighs]

24:32.930 --> 24:36.040
I'm sorry, Harlan,
but I think I'm pretty fucked.

24:36.240 --> 24:37.910
[rapping]

24:38.110 --> 24:42.510
<i>* *</i>

24:42.710 --> 24:45.050
I'm getting you out of this.

24:45.250 --> 24:51.890
<i>* *</i>

24:53.890 --> 24:56.790
- Sorry, Harlan,
this conversation's over.

24:56.990 --> 25:03.870
<i>* *</i>

25:10.270 --> 25:13.140
<i>[ominous music]</i>

25:13.340 --> 25:20.410
<i>* *</i>

25:25.450 --> 25:27.390
Ramsey!

25:28.690 --> 25:30.860
We need to open up
the freezer downstairs.

25:31.060 --> 25:31.990
Why?

25:32.190 --> 25:34.360
- We've got 18 bodies
coming in,

25:34.560 --> 25:35.960
including Officer Trent Miller.

25:36.160 --> 25:37.600
Where were they found?

25:37.800 --> 25:39.630
Same construction site.

25:39.830 --> 25:41.370
Someone called in
an anonymous tip.

25:41.570 --> 25:43.840
<i>* *</i>

25:44.040 --> 25:44.910
Anonymous?

25:45.110 --> 25:48.010
<i>* *</i>

25:48.210 --> 25:49.840
[sighs]

25:50.040 --> 25:53.820
<i>* *</i>

25:54.010 --> 25:55.680
Guys, go home.

25:55.880 --> 25:57.290
Don't go anywhere else.

25:57.480 --> 25:59.420
- I'm not waiting around.
- Harlan, please.

25:59.620 --> 26:01.660
I need you to trust me on this.

26:03.220 --> 26:04.890
Get Cyrus out.

26:05.090 --> 26:06.860
Then I'll trust you.

26:07.060 --> 26:09.200
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

26:09.400 --> 26:13.670
<i>* *</i>

26:20.210 --> 26:23.240
[doorbell rings]

26:24.250 --> 26:25.750
- Sorry.
I have to watch him.

26:25.950 --> 26:26.920
I didn't know where else
to take him.

26:27.110 --> 26:28.180
It's OK.

26:28.380 --> 26:29.450
Baron's still
completely knocked out.

26:29.650 --> 26:31.490
[door creaks]

26:31.690 --> 26:32.520
[gasps]

26:32.720 --> 26:33.960
<i>[tense music]</i>

26:34.150 --> 26:35.360
Hey!

26:35.560 --> 26:36.590
Fear and pain.

26:36.790 --> 26:39.590
<i>* *</i>

26:39.790 --> 26:41.100
Fear and pain.

26:41.300 --> 26:42.730
<i>* *</i>

26:42.930 --> 26:45.100
F-f-fear and pain.

26:45.300 --> 26:49.600
<i>* *</i>

26:49.800 --> 26:51.840
He knows who Baron is.

26:52.040 --> 26:54.810
[grunting]

26:55.010 --> 26:57.410
[moaning]

26:57.610 --> 26:58.780
Come on.

26:58.980 --> 27:00.750
[door slams]

27:00.950 --> 27:02.280
You heard us the whole time?

27:02.480 --> 27:03.650
- Remember when they
brought us in for interviews

27:03.850 --> 27:05.350
and we could all
hear each other?

27:05.550 --> 27:06.960
It was the white noise machine.

27:07.150 --> 27:08.960
It did something,
and she knows it.

27:09.160 --> 27:11.960
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

27:12.160 --> 27:14.860
<i>* *</i>

27:15.060 --> 27:16.030
What is that?

27:16.230 --> 27:17.970
I think it was Ramsey.

27:18.170 --> 27:23.300
<i>* *</i>

27:23.500 --> 27:25.440
- [device beeps]
<i>- This is Garrett Briggs.</i>

27:25.640 --> 27:29.740
<i>This message is for my kids,</i>
<i>Harlan and Luna.</i>

27:29.940 --> 27:32.850
<i>Hey, guys, I don't know if I'm</i>
<i>gonna make it out of here.</i>

27:33.050 --> 27:36.650
<i>And if I don't, I want to</i>
<i>make sure there's a message.</i>

27:36.850 --> 27:39.020
<i>Luna, I want you to know</i>
<i>that things are</i>

27:39.220 --> 27:41.260
<i>gonna change, all right?</i>

27:41.460 --> 27:42.720
<i>I know you haven't made</i>
<i>the kind of friends</i>

27:42.920 --> 27:45.730
<i>you were hoping to find</i>
<i>the last few years.</i>

27:45.930 --> 27:49.000
<i>I promise you,</i>
<i>you'll find your people.</i>

27:49.200 --> 27:51.030
<i>* *</i>

27:51.230 --> 27:52.570
<i>You'll find your pack.</i>

27:52.770 --> 27:55.700
<i>[breathing heavily]</i>

27:55.900 --> 27:58.640
<i>Harlan, I know all we do</i>
<i>right now is argue.</i>

27:58.840 --> 28:01.240
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't</i>
<i>figure out how to fix that.</i>

28:01.440 --> 28:03.580
<i>Do me a favor</i>
<i>and remember when--</i>

28:03.780 --> 28:05.850
<i>when things were good</i>
<i>between us.</i>

28:06.050 --> 28:08.780
<i>Remember that I took you</i>
<i>to every R-rated horror movie</i>

28:08.980 --> 28:13.120
<i>you ever wanted to see,</i>
<i>even though you were only 10.</i>

28:13.320 --> 28:14.690
<i>[chuckles]</i>
<i>And I was the one</i>

28:14.890 --> 28:16.520
<i>who ended up</i>
<i>having nightmares.</i>

28:16.720 --> 28:19.960
<i>Remember that I love you</i>
<i>even though I'm not your--</i>

28:20.160 --> 28:22.760
<i>even though you don't</i>
<i>see me as your real--</i>

28:22.960 --> 28:25.630
[breathing heavily]

28:25.830 --> 28:26.630
[device beeps]

28:26.830 --> 28:29.970
<i>* *</i>

28:30.170 --> 28:32.510
- We need to tell him
about Baron.

28:32.710 --> 28:34.910
<i>* *</i>

28:35.110 --> 28:36.950
Everything changes now.

28:37.140 --> 28:39.050
Once the FBI
gets here, I'm out,

28:39.250 --> 28:40.950
so I need you to talk to me--

28:41.150 --> 28:42.520
and not in vague allusions.

28:42.720 --> 28:44.990
I need details.

28:45.190 --> 28:47.290
Do you trust me?

28:50.660 --> 28:52.260
No.

28:54.200 --> 28:55.160
Not at first--

28:55.360 --> 28:57.200
not until I saw you myself

28:57.400 --> 28:59.400
with Harlan and Luna.

28:59.600 --> 29:01.570
That's when it changed.

29:01.770 --> 29:08.310
<i>* *</i>

29:08.510 --> 29:11.480
[indistinct chatter]

29:11.680 --> 29:18.550
<i>* *</i>

29:32.730 --> 29:35.570
<i>[ominous music]</i>

29:35.770 --> 29:42.640
<i>* *</i>

31:29.980 --> 31:33.350
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

31:33.550 --> 31:40.590
<i>* *</i>

32:00.950 --> 32:02.480
- [device beeps]
<i>- This is a message</i>

32:02.680 --> 32:04.920
<i>for my kids, Harlan and Luna.</i>

32:05.120 --> 32:09.690
<i>Hey, guys, I don't know if I'm</i>
<i>gonna make it out of here.</i>

32:09.890 --> 32:11.290
- I keep asking him
where he saw Baron,

32:11.490 --> 32:14.460
and all he keeps saying is
parking garage.

32:14.660 --> 32:16.800
So it had to be that night
when I took him to work.

32:17.000 --> 32:18.870
Not parking lot.

32:19.070 --> 32:20.800
I know.

32:21.000 --> 32:22.970
Parking garage.

32:23.170 --> 32:24.910
Wait.

32:25.110 --> 32:27.840
How would Danny
know it was Baron?

32:28.040 --> 32:29.410
He would have seen
the werewolf.

32:29.610 --> 32:30.440
Not parking lot!

32:30.640 --> 32:32.310
Jesus, Danny!

32:32.510 --> 32:35.950
We get it--parking garage,
not parking lot.

32:38.290 --> 32:41.160
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:41.360 --> 32:48.400
<i>* *</i>

32:53.000 --> 32:56.040
Did you see Ramsey
in the parking garage too?

32:56.240 --> 32:59.810
Remember, I kept saying you met
her in the motel parking lot,

33:00.010 --> 33:02.680
but you kept saying
parking garage?

33:03.640 --> 33:05.580
Is that what you were
trying to tell me yesterday?

33:06.980 --> 33:10.480
Did you see Ramsey
in the garage where I work?

33:13.220 --> 33:15.220
Did she talk to you?
Did she say something?

33:15.420 --> 33:17.660
- N-nice to meet you.

33:17.860 --> 33:18.960
<i>Do you remember me?</i>

33:19.160 --> 33:23.030
We never got the chance
to say hello.

33:23.230 --> 33:24.300
It's nice to meet you, Danny.

33:24.500 --> 33:25.800
What does that mean?

33:26.000 --> 33:27.030
Shake.

33:29.270 --> 33:30.870
She shook your hand?

33:31.070 --> 33:33.740
That's it?
That's all that she did?

33:35.140 --> 33:36.240
The day of the full moon,

33:36.440 --> 33:37.480
Ramsey came to my house
to talk to me.

33:37.680 --> 33:39.250
- That's all right,
shaking my hand

33:39.450 --> 33:40.880
is not an admission of guilt.

33:41.080 --> 33:47.490
<i>* *</i>

33:47.690 --> 33:50.560
She talked to you
right after me.

33:50.760 --> 33:52.790
Did she do the same thing?

33:52.990 --> 33:53.930
Kind of.

33:54.130 --> 33:56.060
<i>I was on the ground,</i>

33:56.260 --> 33:58.100
<i>and she held out her hand</i>
<i>to help me up.</i>

33:58.300 --> 34:02.470
<i>* *</i>

34:02.670 --> 34:04.570
- That's why Baron
didn't kill him.

34:04.770 --> 34:06.470
He saw Danny hit you.

34:06.670 --> 34:07.810
But after Ramsey
shook his hand,

34:08.010 --> 34:09.310
Danny wasn't a threat anymore.

34:09.510 --> 34:11.580
She marked him.

34:11.780 --> 34:13.850
What if she knows everything?

34:15.150 --> 34:17.320
Maybe she's the voice
on the phone.

34:17.520 --> 34:18.790
[door bangs open]

34:18.990 --> 34:22.020
- [breathing heavily]
Where is he?

34:22.220 --> 34:26.990
<i>* *</i>

34:27.190 --> 34:28.830
[sighs]

34:29.030 --> 34:31.630
All right, let's put
some clothes on him.

34:31.830 --> 34:33.700
We're taking him
to the hospital.

34:33.900 --> 34:35.340
What if he wakes up?

34:35.540 --> 34:36.400
I came prepared.

34:36.600 --> 34:41.680
<i>* *</i>

34:41.880 --> 34:43.380
Come on, come on.
He's gonna die. Move!

34:43.580 --> 34:46.280
Move!
Start the car!

34:46.480 --> 34:53.550
<i>* *</i>

34:57.090 --> 34:58.160
You're not coming.

35:00.330 --> 35:02.930
- My dad's gonna be here soon
to pick us up.

35:03.130 --> 35:04.500
What about Ramsey?

35:04.700 --> 35:07.400
- We don't even know
if we're right about her.

35:07.600 --> 35:08.670
That's a pretty big guess.

35:08.870 --> 35:11.270
I don't want you to go.

35:11.470 --> 35:12.470
- I'm sorry.
[horn honks]

35:12.670 --> 35:14.410
Everett, come on.

35:14.610 --> 35:17.710
- If Baron dies,
we go back to normal.

35:19.680 --> 35:22.480
That fixes everything.

35:23.480 --> 35:25.050
I'm sorry.

35:25.250 --> 35:32.090
<i>* *</i>

35:35.660 --> 35:37.400
Need some help, please!

35:37.600 --> 35:38.970
This boy's been stabbed.

35:39.170 --> 35:41.640
<i>* *</i>

35:41.840 --> 35:43.640
- He's in the ER getting
checked out by doctors now.

35:43.840 --> 35:46.070
- Did Garrett say what to do?
- Don't come in.

35:46.270 --> 35:49.210
He said it might take hours
and we should just go home.

35:49.410 --> 35:52.010
Everett, come on.

35:52.210 --> 35:54.580
I'm not going home.

35:54.780 --> 35:56.020
They can't connect us to Baron.

35:56.220 --> 35:57.450
Everett.

35:57.650 --> 35:58.550
Hey!

35:58.750 --> 36:00.750
[keys jingling]

36:01.860 --> 36:02.920
I'm not leaving him alone.

36:03.120 --> 36:05.590
- Everett can take care
of himself.

36:05.790 --> 36:08.530
- But he's part
of the pack, right?

36:08.730 --> 36:10.560
There is no pack, Harlan.

36:10.760 --> 36:15.240
<i>* *</i>

36:15.440 --> 36:16.900
There never was.

36:17.100 --> 36:23.980
<i>* *</i>

36:35.060 --> 36:37.690
[doorbell rings]

36:37.890 --> 36:39.830
- No.
No, Danny.

36:40.030 --> 36:41.760
Hey, Danny,
don't open the door!

36:43.260 --> 36:44.330
Hey!

36:44.530 --> 36:46.570
Hey, there's my little guy.

36:46.770 --> 36:49.000
Dad.

36:49.200 --> 36:53.270
<i>* *</i>

36:53.470 --> 36:54.740
What is this?

36:54.940 --> 36:57.280
- Blake, social services
is gonna be looking after you

36:57.480 --> 36:59.850
and Danny for a while.

37:00.050 --> 37:02.850
- Hey, look, they're
not giving me a choice.

37:03.050 --> 37:04.850
But since Danny
has special needs,

37:05.050 --> 37:06.420
they're saying you're not
gonna be together.

37:06.620 --> 37:08.420
I have to file
some kind of appeal.

37:08.620 --> 37:09.620
No.

37:09.820 --> 37:11.260
Can they do this?

37:11.460 --> 37:13.790
I know it's my fault. I know.

37:13.990 --> 37:16.400
I--I know that I'm
the real problem here.

37:16.600 --> 37:17.530
- No.
- I know that.

37:17.730 --> 37:19.870
No, Dad. Wait, please.

37:20.070 --> 37:21.100
Dad, this is not your fault.
This is my fault.

37:21.300 --> 37:22.270
Please, you can't let them
do this.

37:22.470 --> 37:23.300
[Danny whimpers]

37:23.500 --> 37:25.270
Wait!

37:25.470 --> 37:27.310
[gasps]

37:27.510 --> 37:29.340
<i>* *</i>

37:29.540 --> 37:32.980
- You know, you have
really beautiful skin.

37:33.180 --> 37:35.050
It wasn't always
like that, was it?

37:35.250 --> 37:37.550
<i>* *</i>

37:37.750 --> 37:40.250
No.

37:40.450 --> 37:44.760
- Something helped
change things for the better.

37:44.960 --> 37:48.760
What would you think
if we could help Danny change?

37:50.300 --> 37:52.330
Danny?

37:52.530 --> 37:55.340
That's right, Blake.

37:55.540 --> 37:57.570
Just like you.

37:57.770 --> 38:00.540
- What if I don't
want him to change?

38:00.740 --> 38:02.640
I think you do.

38:02.840 --> 38:03.840
You can say that you
don't want Danny

38:04.040 --> 38:05.850
to be any different

38:06.050 --> 38:07.680
because it's
the right thing to say.

38:07.880 --> 38:09.350
It's what you're
supposed to say.

38:09.550 --> 38:12.620
<i>* *</i>

38:12.820 --> 38:15.490
But even Harlan would know
you're lying

38:15.690 --> 38:17.490
without listening
to your heart.

38:17.690 --> 38:22.660
<i>* *</i>

38:29.370 --> 38:31.510
[indistinct chatter]

38:31.710 --> 38:32.870
- They're not
letting me through.

38:33.070 --> 38:34.110
But they said if you
need to talk to Garrett,

38:34.310 --> 38:35.240
they'll let you by.

38:35.440 --> 38:37.210
- They're probably
calling the cops.

38:37.410 --> 38:38.280
This is getting complicated.

38:38.480 --> 38:39.680
I need to talk to my dad.

38:39.880 --> 38:41.210
Wait for me.

38:43.020 --> 38:44.520
[sighs]

38:48.760 --> 38:49.690
[sighs]

38:50.960 --> 38:52.790
[groans]

38:55.330 --> 38:58.230
[breathes deeply]

39:02.940 --> 39:05.810
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

39:06.010 --> 39:10.080
<i>* *</i>

39:10.280 --> 39:11.550
Dad?

39:11.750 --> 39:13.980
- We need to talk
about something.

39:14.180 --> 39:16.320
Wait.

39:16.520 --> 39:19.550
Wait--wait a second, Dad.

39:19.750 --> 39:22.690
- You're not really doing this.
- You're right. I'm not.

39:22.890 --> 39:24.590
You did this.

39:24.790 --> 39:26.860
These are the results
of your behavior.

39:27.060 --> 39:28.900
You need to accept
responsibility for that.

39:29.100 --> 39:30.230
You want to 5150 me?

39:30.430 --> 39:32.300
You're a minor. It's a 5585.

39:32.500 --> 39:34.340
It's a 72-hour hold.

39:34.530 --> 39:36.340
I'm not a danger to myself.

39:36.540 --> 39:37.770
But you might be to others.

39:37.970 --> 39:39.540
- Like who?
- You threatened your mother.

39:39.740 --> 39:43.010
[breathing heavily]

39:43.210 --> 39:44.850
Is that what she said?

39:47.010 --> 39:49.780
- You came threateningly
close to your mother.

39:51.690 --> 39:53.290
She swore that you
were gonna become

39:53.490 --> 39:55.990
physically violent with her.

39:56.190 --> 39:57.430
I never touched her.

39:57.620 --> 40:00.430
- You ripped the car keys
from her hands!

40:00.630 --> 40:03.100
The arson detective said
that you brought a kid in here

40:03.300 --> 40:06.370
with a knife in his chest.

40:06.570 --> 40:07.640
Everett, for Christ's sake,

40:07.830 --> 40:09.400
there's blood
all over your room.

40:09.600 --> 40:12.970
<i>* *</i>

40:13.170 --> 40:16.710
Dad, please, please.

40:16.910 --> 40:19.480
Don't do this, OK?
This is not gonna help.

40:19.680 --> 40:21.520
Please.
Dad, please don't do this!

40:21.720 --> 40:23.180
This is not gonna help, OK?

40:23.380 --> 40:26.290
Dad, please don't do this!

40:26.490 --> 40:29.420
<i>* *</i>

40:32.490 --> 40:34.930
<i>[tense music]</i>

40:35.130 --> 40:38.000
Yo.

40:38.200 --> 40:39.900
What are you doing here?

40:40.100 --> 40:42.100
Weekly STI check?

40:42.300 --> 40:45.010
I'm just fucking with you.

40:45.200 --> 40:47.010
- Is that a bag full of--

40:47.210 --> 40:48.810
Toys for sick children.

40:49.010 --> 40:50.780
Yeah.

40:52.550 --> 40:54.480
Where do you think
I got the epinephrine?

40:54.680 --> 40:56.680
You get everything here?

40:58.120 --> 40:59.720
From my dad.

40:59.920 --> 41:03.360
He's still a piece of shit
but he hooks me up.

41:05.890 --> 41:07.930
Cody.

41:08.130 --> 41:11.100
<i>* *</i>

41:11.300 --> 41:13.730
What's your last name?

41:13.930 --> 41:15.340
Malcolm.

41:15.530 --> 41:16.500
You didn't know that?

41:16.700 --> 41:23.480
<i>* *</i>

41:24.580 --> 41:26.380
Where are you taking me?

41:26.580 --> 41:28.450
To meet your mother.

41:28.650 --> 41:31.390
She's been trying
to find you for a long time.

41:31.580 --> 41:33.720
She started the wildfire.

41:33.920 --> 41:35.160
She knew it was
the only thing that

41:35.350 --> 41:36.860
could bring you out of hiding.

41:38.560 --> 41:42.060
She killed all those people
just to find you.

41:42.260 --> 41:46.370
Some kind of motherly
love, isn't it?

41:46.570 --> 41:49.700
<i>* *</i>

41:49.900 --> 41:53.110
[roars]

41:53.310 --> 41:56.840
<i>* *</i>

41:57.040 --> 41:58.910
[flames crackling]

41:59.110 --> 42:05.990
<i>* *</i>

42:14.290 --> 42:17.160
[roars]

42:17.360 --> 42:24.440
<i>* *</i>

42:31.040 --> 42:33.910
[snarling]

42:34.110 --> 42:40.990
<i>* *</i>

42:46.830 --> 42:49.630
- The nurse told me he was
being taken to surgery.

42:51.770 --> 42:53.800
Nobody can seem
to find him now.

42:57.740 --> 43:00.170
Does that mean anything to you?

43:00.370 --> 43:02.710
It does.

43:02.910 --> 43:05.050
It's from a former firefighter,
guy named Malcolm.

43:05.240 --> 43:07.450
Before Cyrus, he was our
number one arson suspect.

43:07.650 --> 43:09.480
[sighs]

43:12.220 --> 43:13.450
You think he took this kid?

43:13.650 --> 43:15.820
I don't know.

43:16.020 --> 43:18.230
I do know that the FBI is here.

43:18.420 --> 43:20.390
I'm out.

43:20.590 --> 43:23.460
<i>* *</i>

43:23.660 --> 43:26.930
Garrett, you asked me
to trust you.

43:27.130 --> 43:32.210
I'm asking--can you
trust me now?

43:32.410 --> 43:37.910
<i>* *</i>

43:38.110 --> 43:40.080
[sighs]

43:40.280 --> 43:47.120
<i>* *</i>

44:09.280 --> 44:10.880
Harlan Briggs.

44:14.250 --> 44:15.580
You're under arrest
for the murder

44:15.780 --> 44:16.920
of Officer Trenton Miller.

44:17.120 --> 44:20.450
Turn around and put your hands
behind your back.

44:20.650 --> 44:23.460
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

44:23.660 --> 44:25.190
<i>* *</i>

44:25.390 --> 44:31.260
<i>- * You can try to resist,</i>
<i>try to hide from my kiss *</i>

44:31.460 --> 44:33.030
I found you.

44:33.230 --> 44:37.600
<i>- * But you know that you</i>
<i>can't fight the moonlight *</i>

44:37.800 --> 44:42.080
<i>* Deep in the dark,</i>
<i>you'll surrender your heart *</i>

44:42.280 --> 44:45.110
<i>* But you know, but you know *</i>

44:45.310 --> 44:49.050
<i>* That you can't fight</i>
<i>the moonlight *</i>

44:49.250 --> 44:50.680
<i>* No *</i>

44:50.880 --> 44:54.550
<i>* You can't fight it *</i>

44:54.750 --> 44:58.560
<i>* It's gonna get</i>
<i>to your heart *</i>

44:58.760 --> 45:05.800
<i>* *</i>

45:30.490 --> 45:31.830
[metallic scraping]

45:32.030 --> 45:33.960
<i>* You can try to resist *</i>

45:34.160 --> 45:38.230
<i>* Try to hide from my kiss,</i>
<i>but you know *</i>

45:38.430 --> 45:43.200
<i>* But you know that you</i>
<i>can't fight the moonlight *</i>

45:43.400 --> 45:47.210
<i>* *</i>

45:47.410 --> 45:48.640
Where is he?

45:51.210 --> 45:55.020
- You think I brought you here
for a touching reunion?

45:55.210 --> 45:57.380
I brought you here
so I could kill you.

45:57.580 --> 45:58.890
So you could try to kill me.

45:59.090 --> 46:01.820
Let's not get
ahead of ourselves.

46:02.020 --> 46:06.390
- Your head is exactly
what I'm hoping for.

46:07.730 --> 46:10.260
An ax made of silver.

46:10.460 --> 46:12.570
<i>* *</i>

46:12.770 --> 46:16.170
- No.
[ax clatters]

46:16.370 --> 46:18.270
Silver-plated.

46:18.470 --> 46:21.310
I used most of the silver
for the bullets.

46:22.780 --> 46:24.310
[gunshots]

46:27.310 --> 46:33.490
<i>* *</i>

46:33.690 --> 46:36.290
[gunshots]

46:36.490 --> 46:37.760
[grunts]

46:39.660 --> 46:46.730
<i>* *</i>

46:48.400 --> 46:50.470
[rapid gunshots]

46:57.840 --> 47:01.350
[groans weakly]

47:01.550 --> 47:04.480
[gunshots]

47:04.680 --> 47:11.760
<i>* *</i>

47:28.440 --> 47:29.980
[gun cocking]

47:36.120 --> 47:37.450
[breathing heavily]

47:37.650 --> 47:44.460
<i>* *</i>

47:44.660 --> 47:45.790
[hollow bang]

47:47.590 --> 47:54.530
<i>* *</i>

48:15.220 --> 48:17.260
[gasps]

48:21.660 --> 48:24.530
[phone buzzing]

48:24.730 --> 48:26.800
[sighs]

48:29.770 --> 48:33.510
<i>* *</i>

48:33.710 --> 48:35.140
[phone dings]

48:35.340 --> 48:37.340
Who is this?

48:37.540 --> 48:40.510
Besides the anonymous caller
who found 18 bodies?

48:40.710 --> 48:42.780
<i>- You think</i>
<i>you made them a pack?</i>

48:42.980 --> 48:44.450
<i>They wouldn't be</i>
<i>alive without me.</i>

48:44.650 --> 48:47.620
<i>I've helped them</i>
<i>every step of the way,</i>

48:47.820 --> 48:49.690
<i>and I'm still helping them.</i>

48:49.890 --> 48:51.090
How?

48:51.290 --> 48:54.260
<i>- Because I</i>
<i>called Garrett first.</i>

48:56.260 --> 48:58.830
[gasps]

48:59.030 --> 49:01.800
[breathing heavily]

49:02.000 --> 49:08.410
<i>* *</i>

49:18.450 --> 49:19.590
Who are you?

49:19.790 --> 49:24.960
<i>* *</i>

49:40.040 --> 49:42.310
I'm Harlan and Luna's mother.

49:42.510 --> 49:47.680
<i>* *</i>

49:47.880 --> 49:50.950
Baron is their brother.

49:51.150 --> 49:52.850
He's gonna die
if we don't help him.

49:53.050 --> 49:56.090
That's all you need
to know right now.

49:56.290 --> 50:00.390
Blake, Everett,
Harlan, and Luna--

50:00.590 --> 50:02.300
only they could do it.

50:04.500 --> 50:09.870
Only a pack could
make him human again.

50:10.070 --> 50:12.770
Do they know that?

50:12.970 --> 50:15.780
They're learning.

50:15.970 --> 50:18.450
They don't quite trust me yet.

50:18.640 --> 50:21.510
Yeah, neither do I.

50:21.710 --> 50:23.420
You should.

50:24.980 --> 50:27.350
Let me show you why.

50:27.550 --> 50:33.560
<i>* *</i>

50:33.760 --> 50:35.900
Everett is strong.

50:36.090 --> 50:38.400
Blake is fast.

50:38.600 --> 50:43.570
Harlan and Luna
have sound and smell.

50:46.710 --> 50:48.810
Baron, you have
what used to be called

50:49.010 --> 50:51.410
the power of transmutation.

50:51.610 --> 50:54.350
- I turn people
into werewolves.

50:54.550 --> 50:57.180
- Every member of the pack
has an ability.

50:57.380 --> 51:00.050
Let me show you what I can do.

51:00.250 --> 51:07.330
<i>* *</i>

51:17.370 --> 51:20.410
[breathing heavily]

51:20.610 --> 51:27.480
<i>* *</i>

51:28.680 --> 51:31.550
<i>[whooshing]</i>

51:31.750 --> 51:38.590
<i>* *</i>

51:51.040 --> 51:55.040
<i>[eerie whooshing]</i>

51:56.780 --> 51:58.850
[breathing heavily]

51:59.040 --> 52:06.090
<i>* *</i>

52:13.330 --> 52:15.030
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

52:17.000 --> 52:19.730
[growls]
[gunshots]

52:19.930 --> 52:21.900
[snarling]

52:22.100 --> 52:29.180
<i>* *</i>

52:32.280 --> 52:34.150
[breathing heavily]

52:34.350 --> 52:38.050
<i>* *</i>

52:38.250 --> 52:41.390
[grunting]

52:46.930 --> 52:49.200
You're not as strong
as you think you are.

52:49.400 --> 52:50.830
You've been human for too long.

52:51.030 --> 52:53.070
[growls]

52:53.270 --> 52:55.400
[grunts]

52:55.600 --> 52:59.470
- [snarls]
[bones crunching]

52:59.670 --> 53:02.040
[groaning]

53:02.240 --> 53:04.410
[gunshot]

53:04.610 --> 53:06.150
[grunting]

53:09.280 --> 53:11.850
You need him alive.

53:14.020 --> 53:15.960
[grunts]

53:16.150 --> 53:18.990
[handcuffs click]

53:19.190 --> 53:26.270
<i>* *</i>

53:32.340 --> 53:35.040
- You know what would have
happened if he killed me.

53:35.240 --> 53:38.280
- Harlan and Luna
would be next.

53:38.480 --> 53:41.080
- Do you know what
a Trophic Cascade is, Garrett?

53:41.280 --> 53:43.720
- Predator impact
on an ecosystem.

53:43.920 --> 53:49.190
<i>* *</i>

53:49.390 --> 53:50.760
- Then you know what happened
when they brought

53:50.960 --> 53:55.130
the wolves back
to Yellowstone National Park.

53:55.330 --> 53:59.030
The elk...

53:59.230 --> 54:02.540
are no longer safe.

54:02.740 --> 54:06.140
- Because the wolves
kept them in check.

54:06.340 --> 54:11.780
It had such a profound
and cascading effect,

54:11.980 --> 54:15.480
changed the flow of rivers.

54:15.680 --> 54:19.690
That's the power
of an apex predator.

54:19.890 --> 54:23.990
- You want Baron because
you want more wolves.

54:24.190 --> 54:27.430
I want my family back.

54:27.630 --> 54:29.560
What if I try to stop you?

54:29.760 --> 54:31.460
[scoffs]

54:31.660 --> 54:34.870
This isn't a moral quandary,
Garrett.

54:35.070 --> 54:38.310
I knew you were a good parent.

54:38.500 --> 54:41.140
I need you to help
protect our children.

54:41.340 --> 54:44.110
<i>* *</i>

54:44.310 --> 54:49.080
Baron is gonna be
just like Harlan and Luna.

54:49.280 --> 54:51.680
He's gonna need both of us.

54:53.420 --> 54:56.620
Think about it.

54:56.820 --> 55:00.560
Blake and her brother
can have a normal life.

55:02.260 --> 55:06.830
Everett never has
to feel anxious again.

55:07.030 --> 55:09.470
<i>* *</i>

55:09.670 --> 55:13.640
Luna can have the pack
that she's been searching for.

55:13.840 --> 55:16.710
<i>* *</i>

55:16.910 --> 55:20.280
And Harlan can have
the father

55:20.480 --> 55:22.180
that he has always wanted...

55:22.380 --> 55:25.650
<i>* *</i>

55:25.850 --> 55:27.950
In you.

55:28.150 --> 55:29.860
<i>* *</i>

55:30.060 --> 55:32.360
Not the human father.

55:32.560 --> 55:35.960
No, the wolf.

55:36.160 --> 55:38.970
[growling]

55:39.160 --> 55:46.240
<i>* *</i>

55:48.570 --> 55:50.780
<i>- * Can't fight</i>
<i>the moonlight *</i>

55:50.980 --> 55:55.720
<i>* Deep in the dark,</i>
<i>you'll surrender your heart *</i>

55:55.910 --> 55:58.650
<i>* But you know, but you know *</i>

55:58.850 --> 56:02.860
<i>* That you can't fight</i>
<i>the moonlight *</i>
